.TH "g2d_wait_finish" 9 "g2d_wait_finish" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
g2d_wait_finish \- wait for the G2D engine to finish the current runqueue node
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" g2d_wait_finish
.BI "(struct g2d_data *g2d "  ","
.BI "struct drm_file *file "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "g2d" 12
G2D state object
.IP "file" 12
if not zero, only wait if the current runqueue node belongs
to the DRM file
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Should the engine not become idle after a 100ms timeout, a hardware
reset is issued.
